    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-06-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="152" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                <head>No. 152.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Sir <persName type="to">Edward
                                        Thornton</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-06-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 10,
                                        1872</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                                receipt of your note of the 17th ultimo, informing me of the
                                appointment of Captain Cameron, of the royal artillery, as Her
                                Britannic Majesty’s commissioner to survey the northwest boundary,
                                and that Her Majesty’s government would be glad to know the views of
                                this Government in regard to the commencement of the operations, and
                                stating that if it should appear to be expedient, orders would be
                                given to Captain Cameron to proceed to Washington for the purpose of
                                making the necessary arrangements in concert with the commissioner
                                who may be appointed on the part of this Government.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to announce to you, for the information of Her
                                Majesty’s government, that the President has appointed Archibald
                                Campbell, esq., commissioner on the part of the United States.</p>
                <p>With reference to the points upon which you desire information, I
                                have to inform you that they will receive early attention, and I
                                shall then recur to the subject.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
